fingerprintWrite

public boolean fingerprintWrite(byte[] audioData)
                         throws GnException
Provides uncompressed audio data to a file information object for fingerprint generation.

Parameters:
audioData - [in] set Pointer to audio data buffer that matches the audio format described in fingerprint_begin().
Returns:
bool Checks whether the fingerprint generation has received enough audio data

Remarks:

The provided audio data must be uncompressed PCM data and must match the format given to fingerprintBegin(). True is returned when the fingerprinting process has received enough audio data to perform its processing. Any further provided audio data is ignored. The application must provide audio data until true is returned to successfully generate an audio fingerprint. The application must complete the fingerprinting process by calling fingerprintEnd() when either the audio data terminates, or after true is returned. Use the MusicID-File fingerprinting APIs either before processing has begun, or during a IGnMusicIdFileEvents or IGnMusicIdFileInfoEvents delegate method call.
Throws:
GnException

fingerprintBegin

public void fingerprintBegin(long audioSampleRate,
                             long audioSampleSize,
                             long audioChannels)
                      throws GnException
Initializes fingerprint generation.

Parameters:
audioSampleRate - [in] set Sample frequency of audio to be provided: 11 kHz, 22 kHz, or 44 kHz
audioSampleSize - [in] set Sample rate of audio to be provided (in 8-bit, 16-bit, or 32-bit bytes per sample)
audioChannels - [in] set Number of channels for audio to be provided (1 or 2)

Remarks:

The MusicID-File fingerprinting APIs allow applications to provide audio data as a method of identification. This enables MusicID-File to perform identification based on the audio itself, as opposed to performing identification using only the associated metadata. Use the MusicID-File fingerprinting APIs either before processing has begun, or during a IGnMusicIdFileEvents or IGnMusicIdFileInfoEvents delegate method call.
Throws:
GnException

fingerprintWrite

public boolean fingerprintWrite(byte[] audioData,
                                long audioDataSize)
                         throws GnException
Provides uncompressed audio data for fingerprint generation.

Parameters:
audioData - [in] pointer to audio data buffer that matches the audio format described in FingerprintBegin().
audioDataSize - [in] size of audio data buffer (in bytes)
Returns:
bool Checks whether the fingerprint generation has received enough audio data

Remarks:

The provided audio data must be uncompressed PCM data and must match the format given to fingerprintBegin(). Returns true value when the fingerprinting process has received enough audio data to perform its processing. Any further provided audio data is ignored. The application must provide audio data until true is returned to successfully generate an audio fingerprint. The application must complete the fingerprinting process by calling FingerprintEnd() when either the audio data terminates, or after true is returned. Use the MusicID-File fingerprinting APIs either before processing has begun, or during a IGnMusicIdFileEvents or IGnMusicIdFileInfoEvents delegate method call.
Throws:
GnException

fingerprintEnd

public void fingerprintEnd()
                    throws GnException
Finalizes fingerprint generation.

Remarks:

The application must complete the fingerprinting process by calling fingerprint_end when either the audio data terminates, or after receiving a GNSDK_TRUE value. Use the MusicID-File fingerprinting APIs either before processing has begun, or during a IGnMusicIdFileEvents or IGnMusicIdFileInfoEvents delegate method call.

Throws:
GnException

The File Info object's state value indicates what kind of response is available for a FileInfo object after MusicID-File. In the case of an error, error info can be retrieved from the FileInfo object.
